Written to `tools/title-loop/docs/4-4ecc581/feedback.md`. Here's a summary of the analysis:

---

**Failure 1 — Baked Eggs** (`Got: ''`):
The title is split across 2 lines. `buildCandidates` correctly builds the 2-line join `"Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce & Coriander"`, but the **dedup "shorter wins" rule destroys it** — the first line alone (`"Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce"`) is a substring of the join and is shorter, so the join is evicted. The first-line fragment and dangling `"& Coriander"` are left, neither of which yields the correct result.

**Failure 2 — Finnish Flatbreads** (`Got: 'FINNISH MILK FLATBREADS'`):
The file has two recipes, both with ALL_CAPS headings. `FINNISH MILK FLATBREADS` is elected `firstStructuralHeading` and gets **+0.10 structural bonus + position factor**. `FINNISH POTATO FLATBREADS` (later in the doc) gets neither. The elevated score of the first title raises the threshold past what the second title can achieve without any bonus — it's filtered out before the multi-title guard runs.

**Failure 3 — Saffron Wheat Buns** (`Got: 'FRON WHEAT BUNS (VARIATION 1)'`):
An OCR corruption of the *previous* recipe's heading (`FRON WHEAT BUNS` ← `SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS`) appears early and passes `isStructuralHeading`, wrongly claiming the `firstStructuralHeading` slot and its +0.10 bonus. The real title spans 2 lines (`SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK` / `/ COTTAGE CHEESE (VARIATION D)`); the continuation logic never fires because the base heading is wrong; and the dedup rule again destroys the correct 2-line join.

**Common themes**: (A) dedup "shorter wins" is too aggressive on split titles, (B) `structuralBonus` awarded to only one candidate hurts multi-recipe pages, (C) OCR fragments from adjacent pages can steal the structural heading slot.
